# Acknowledgments

## Software and Databases

This work relied on the following publicly available tools and resources:

- **UniProt** (https://www.uniprot.org/) — source of the raw protein sequences
- **MAFFT, MUSCLE, Clustal Omega, T-Coffee, Kalign** — multiple sequence alignment
- **TrimAl** — alignment trimming
- **MEME Suite** — motif discovery
- **IQ-TREE** — maximum-likelihood phylogenetic inference
- **MODELLER** — homology structural modeling
- **Biopython, scikit-learn, SciPy, pandas, matplotlib, seaborn** — analysis and visualization in Python

We thank the developers and maintainers of these open-source tools and databases.

